<item>
            <title>[PIG-3444] CONCAT with 2+ input parameters fail</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-3444</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This is a continuation work of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-1420&quot; title=&quot;Make CONCAT act on all fields of a tuple, instead of just the first two fields of a tuple&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PIG-1420&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PIG-1420&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; since &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-1420&quot; title=&quot;Make CONCAT act on all fields of a tuple, instead of just the first two fields of a tuple&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PIG-1420&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PIG-1420&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is closed. Currently CONCAT fails with more than 2 parameters. The error message is:&lt;br/&gt;
Could not infer the matching function for org.apache.pig.builtin.CONCAT as multiple or none of them fit&lt;/p&gt;</description>
